issue.title: PageScroll directive doesn't watch for keyup/keydown on a tag
issue.body:
Shouldn't the PageScroll directive listen to keyup/keydown for when a user might press the enter key to scroll? Our use case is a dynamic list of links, anchor tags, that need to be tabbable and scrolled to when enter is pressed. Its for accessibility . I've tried the scroll service though I get no errors and it doesn't work. Any thoughts? ``` {{link}}
``` And my component ``` @ViewChild('targetElement') public targetElement: ElementRef; public scollOnEnter(target) { const pageScrollInstance: PageScrollInstance = this.pageScrollService.create({ document: this.document, scrollTarget: target, advancedInlineOffsetCalculation: true, scrollViews: [this.targetElement.nativeElement] }); this.pageScrollService.start(pageScrollInstance); } ```

comment.body:
Hi @mac1253,
the directive listenes for the `click` event at the attached object:
https://github.com/Nolanus/ngx-page-scroll/blob/master/projects/ngx-page-scroll/src/lib/ngx-page-scroll.directive.ts#L23

But I do agree that it is better from a usability perspective to also handle key-events makes sense.
I'll out that on the feature list to be added in on of the next releases.

issue.title: PageScroll directive doesn't watch for keyup/keydown on a tag
issue.body:
Shouldn't the PageScroll directive listen to keyup/keydown for when a user might press the enter key to scroll? Our use case is a dynamic list of links, anchor tags, that need to be tabbable and scrolled to when enter is pressed. Its for accessibility . I've tried the scroll service though I get no errors and it doesn't work. Any thoughts? ``` {{link}}
``` And my component ``` @ViewChild('targetElement') public targetElement: ElementRef; public scollOnEnter(target) { const pageScrollInstance: PageScrollInstance = this.pageScrollService.create({ document: this.document, scrollTarget: target, advancedInlineOffsetCalculation: true, scrollViews: [this.targetElement.nativeElement] }); this.pageScrollService.start(pageScrollInstance); } ```

comment.body:
Hi @mac1253,
the directive listenes for the `click` event at the attached object:
https://github.com/Nolanus/ngx-page-scroll/blob/master/projects/ngx-page-scroll/src/lib/ngx-page-scroll.directive.ts#L23

But I do agree that it is better from a usability perspective to also handle key-events makes sense.
I'll out that on the feature list to be added in on of the next releases.

issue.title: PageScroll directive doesn't watch for keyup/keydown on a tag
issue.body:
Shouldn't the PageScroll directive listen to keyup/keydown for when a user might press the enter key to scroll? Our use case is a dynamic list of links, anchor tags, that need to be tabbable and scrolled to when enter is pressed. Its for accessibility . I've tried the scroll service though I get no errors and it doesn't work. Any thoughts? ``` {{link}}
``` And my component ``` @ViewChild('targetElement') public targetElement: ElementRef; public scollOnEnter(target) { const pageScrollInstance: PageScrollInstance = this.pageScrollService.create({ document: this.document, scrollTarget: target, advancedInlineOffsetCalculation: true, scrollViews: [this.targetElement.nativeElement] }); this.pageScrollService.start(pageScrollInstance); } ```

comment.body:
Hi @mac1253,
the directive listenes for the `click` event at the attached object:
https://github.com/Nolanus/ngx-page-scroll/blob/master/projects/ngx-page-scroll/src/lib/ngx-page-scroll.directive.ts#L23

But I do agree that it is better from a usability perspective to also handle key-events makes sense.
I'll out that on the feature list to be added in on of the next releases.
